    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. i've also been reading that people who fight against these density changes, like the ones in those \"NIMBY\" groups, are basically just standing in the way of progress and making things worse for everyone else. do u think those types of local opposition are a valid part of the planning process or are they just an obstacle to solving the housing problem?",
